%N A095206 Let n = d(1),d(2),...,d(m) be the decimal representation of n and f(k) be the number obtained by deleting all occurrences of digit k from n, then a(n) = Sum_{k=1..m, d(k)!=0} f(d(k)) mod d(k).
%e A095206 a(23) = 3 mod 2 + 2 mod 3 = 1 + 2 = 3.
%e A095206 a(256) = 56 mod 2 + 26 mod 5 + 25 mod 6 =0 + 1 + 1 = 2.
